<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-199-124 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 398 193</DOCID><JOURNAL>Forbes  March 18 1991 v147 n6 p128(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Is Lotus a buy? (Lotus Development Corp.'s stock value) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Shaffer, Richard A.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Lotus Development Corp's stock value has decreased 34 percentsince Mar 1990, while the average value of software company stockhas increased 33 percent, but Lotus could be on its way torecovery.andP;  Lotus has $684 million in sales and the majorityspreadsheet software market share, but its profit margin hasdecreased to 3.4 percent and it faces more competition than everfrom Quattro Pro and Microsoft Excel.andP;  Lotus has lost itstechnical and marketing advantages, and its market share maycontinue to decline, but Lotus sales are increasing at a steadyrate of 20 percent per year.andP;  Lotus has an advantage with itsNotes network software and its consulting division, but it showsthe greatest potential for future products in word processing andpresentation graphics.andP;  The company can succeed if it returns toits original innovation and produces compelling new softwarepackages.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Lotus Development Corp. (Market share).andO;Ticker:    LOTS.andO;Topic:     Market ShareSpreadsheetsStockOutlookCompetition.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>